<subSubSection lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,1739,1944]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,236,1740,1764]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Range:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Corbet" authorityYear="1978" box="[245,445,1739,1764]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gracillimus">
<emphasis box="[245,445,1739,1764]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Sorex gracillimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has its distribution limited to extreme northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1037,1106,1740,1763]" name="South Korea" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Korea</collectingCountry>
at Mt. Baekdu (
<figureCitation box="[1295,1380,1739,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,185,1649]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[340,1247,185,1649]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 12. Range map of Sorex gracillimus in Korea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4571727" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4571727/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). An alleged collection of this shrew at Mt. Jiri in 1983 found no support from a specimen or official collection of this shrew in 
<collectingCountry box="[253,395,1811,1836]" name="South Korea" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">South Korea</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Han" box="[409,538,1812,1836]" firstAuthor="Han" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="17 - 35" refId="ref101656" refString="Han, S. H. (2004 a) Order Insectivora. In: Won, B. O. (Ed.), The mammals of Korea. Dongbang Media Press, Seoul, pp. 17 - 35. [in Korean]" type="book chapter" year="2004" yearSuffix="a">Han 2004a</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, the occurrence of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[992,1132,1811,1836]" name="South Korea" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">South Korea</collectingCountry>
remains problematic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,1739,1944]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1848,1872]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Remarks:</emphasis>
Additional efforts are necessary to determine the status of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1155,1300,1847,1872]" name="North Korea" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">North Korea</collectingCountry>
. Previously, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Corbet" authorityYear="1978" box="[151,308,1883,1908]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gracillimus">
<emphasis box="[151,165,1884,1907]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[180,308,1883,1908]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">gracillimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1766" box="[681,841,1884,1908]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis box="[681,841,1884,1908]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Sorex minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The subspecies inhabiting 
<collectingCountry box="[1159,1227,1884,1907]" name="South Korea" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Korea</collectingCountry>
remains doubtful, but is probably 
<emphasis box="[326,340,1920,1943]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[354,368,1920,1943]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">g</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[382,501,1919,1944]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">hyojironis,</emphasis>
since this subspecies occupies nearby Manchuria.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
